paper_abstract: Let D be a (v, k, lambda)-difference set in an abelian group G, and (v, 31) = 1. If n = 5p(r) with p a prime not dividing v and r a positive integer, then p is a multiplier of D. In the case 31 vertical bar v, we get restrictions on the parameters of such difference sets D for which p may not be a multiplier.
